kubectl label pod <podname> label=labelname

While checking which POD to select the schedular folows the follwing steps
1.adiquate hardware on node 
2.is node running out of resource 
3. request for a specific node, in this it check for a specific label or port on node it needs to attach 
4. volume required 
5. taints and tolerate 6. affinity roles  

 to run a pod on specific schedular user schedularName: <name of schedular> in metadata.spec section
affinity is also one kind of label, but has two types 1. required and 2. preferred. requiredDuringSchedulingIgnoredDuringExecution and  preferredDuringSchedulingIgnoredDuringExecution
